ce:section.ce:para:
The Curry leaves (
                           Murraya koinigii
                        ) were collected from the campus of my native house at Chatra (Jharkhand, India). Lead sulphate (PbSO4), calcium chloride (CaCl2.6H2O), magnesium chloride (MgCl2.6H2O), cadmium sulphate (CdSO4.H2O), sodium chloride (NaCl), aluminium chloride (AlCl3) were purchased from Merk India. Nickel nitrate [(NiNO3)2.6H2O], copper sulphate (CuSO4.5H2O), cobalt nitrate [(CoNO3)2.6H2O], mercuric chloride (HgCl2), potassium chloride (KCl), stannous chloride (SnCl2.2H2O) was acquired from Merk Germany. Ultrapure distilled water was used in whole experiments.
